class MeanAndSpreadFilter[source]

MeanAndSpreadFilter(fs=100.0, window_length_in_seconds=1.0, no_channels=1)

Applies a moving average filter.

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %}

Examples:

{% raw %} 
n = 1000
signal = helpers.mock_signal(n=n, maxv=200, noise=4)

ms_filter = MeanAndSpreadFilter()

signal_mean, signal_var = ms_filter.filter_samples(np.array(signal)[None, :])

plt.plot(range(n), signal); plt.title("Original"); plt.show()
plt.plot(range(n), signal_mean[0]); plt.title("Filtered"); plt.show()
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
assert len(signal) == len(signal_mean[0]) == len(signal_var[0])
{% endraw %}
